    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Cross-Layer Parameter Mismatch in Aerial FAPI VNF P7 Message Handling\n\n### Summary\nThe Aerial FAPI VNF P7 message handler in `fapi_vnf_p7.c` suffers from a cross-layer parameter mismatch between PHY, MAC, and RRC layers when processing TX_DATA.request messages. This mismatch manifests as inconsistent buffer size calculations and data packing operations, leading to potential memory corruption and SFN/slot synchronization errors during runtime.\n\nThe issue occurs because the buffer size calculation in `aerial_nr_send_p7_message` uses the original PDU lengths, while the actual data packing in `aerial_pack_tx_data_request` modifies these lengths based on TLV content. This inconsistency causes the allocated buffer to be either too small or too large for the actual data being packed, resulting in memory access violations or data corruption.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure OAI5G gNB with Aerial FAPI integration enabled\n2. Establish RRC connections with multiple UEs transmitting uplink data\n3. Observe intermittent SFN/slot mismatch errors in the logs:\n   ```\n   sfn slot doesn't match unpacked one! L2->L1 X.X  vs L1->L2 Y.Y\n   ```\n4. Under heavy load conditions, the gNB may crash with segmentation faults or exhibit incorrect data transmission behavior\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_vnf_p7.c`: \n  - Modified buffer size calculation in `aerial_nr_send_p7_message` to use TLV lengths when available, ensuring consistency with actual data packing\n  - Added safety check for TLV array access in `aerial_pack_tx_data_request` to prevent out-of-bounds access\n  - Fixed variable name in error logging message from `i` to `k` for correct TLV index reporting\n"
}